# Bark & Bite - Iranian APT Detection Rules: March 2026 Update
# Version: 3.0
# Last Updated: 2026-03-09
# Credit: Bark & Bite Security
#
# This update covers new Iranian APT activity from July 2025 through March 2026.
# Designed to append to the existing iranian_apt_v2.rules (SID 2000001-2000130).
# New SID range: 2000131-2000230
#
# Threat context: Following the June 2025 twelve-day Iran-Israel war and
# Operation Epic Fury (Feb 28, 2026), Iranian cyber operations are at their
# highest-ever tempo. MuddyWater, CyberAv3ngers, UNC1549, Infy, and
# RedKitten are all actively targeting U.S. and Western critical infrastructure.
#
# References:
#   - CISA Joint Fact Sheet: Iranian Cyber Actors May Target Vulnerable US
#     Networks (Jun 30, 2025; updated Jan 14, 2026)
#   - FBI Urgent Reminder: Iranian Cyber Actors (Mar 3, 2026)
#   - CISA AA23-335A: IRGC-Affiliated CyberAv3ngers (updated Dec 18, 2024)
#   - CISA AA24-241A: Iran-based Ransomware Access Brokers
#   - CISA AA24-290A: Iranian Brute Force and Credential Access
#   - Dragos 2026 OT Cybersecurity Year in Review
#   - Group-IB: Operation Olalampo (Feb 2026)
#   - Mandiant: UNC1549 TWOSTROKE/DEEPROOT (Nov 2025)
#   - Ctrl-Alt-Intel: MuddyWater Exposed (Mar 2026)

#==============================================================================
# SECTION 1: NEW CVE EXPLOITATION - INITIAL ACCESS
# MITRE ATT&CK: T1190 (Exploit Public-Facing Application)
#==============================================================================

# CVE-2026-1281: Ivanti EPMM Unauthenticated RCE via bash arithmetic expansion
# Exploited by MuddyWater; CISA KEV Jan 29, 2026; scanned with Nuclei templates
# CVSS 9.8 - Targets /mifs/rs/api/v2/ endpoint with crafted arithmetic payloads
